                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Is How Your Smartwatch Spies on You]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-how-your-smartwatch-spies-on-you/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/man-checking-his-smartwatch-while-surrounded-by-red-eyes-with-a-close-up-of-the-watch-screen-showing-a-large-eye-symbol.png" length="2563" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Wearables]]></category><category><![CDATA[Privacy]]></category><category><![CDATA[health]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Who watches the watch-watchers?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Wearables haven't made quite the splash some people thought they would. Not quite yet anyway, but there are a lot of people out there wearing smartwatches—I used to be one of them!</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 21:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-how-your-smartwatch-spies-on-you/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Firefox 143 Brings Back Installable Web Apps, Improves Tabs and Cameras, and More]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/firefox-143-brings-back-installable-web-apps-improves-tabs-and-cameras-and-more/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/firefox.jpg" length="147" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Firefox]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Firefox 143 has arrived for desktop platforms, Android, and iOS.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Mozilla Firefox receives major updates roughly every four weeks, giving the web browser a steady stream of bug fixes, new features, and security enhancements. Firefox 143 is now rolling out with the return of installable websites, improvements to tabs and camera access, and much more.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 20:12:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/firefox-143-brings-back-installable-web-apps-improves-tabs-and-cameras-and-more/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Can the AirPods Pro 3 Replace Your Apple Watch? Yes and No]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/can-the-airpods-pro-3-replace-your-apple-watch-yes-and-no/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathaniel Pangaro]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/untitled_artwork-5.jpg" length="1578" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple AirPods Pro 3]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Watch]]></category><category><![CDATA[Fitness]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Watch Series 11]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            AirPods Pro 3 include a heart rate sensor for health tracking, so how does it compare with the Apple Watch?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>With the AirPods Pro 3’s new heart rate monitor, Apple focused heavily on fitness benefits during its September event. In doing so, the company marketed the earbuds as a potential replacement for the Apple Watch in fitness tracking, without explicitly saying so.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 20:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/can-the-airpods-pro-3-replace-your-apple-watch-yes-and-no/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Dolphin Emulator Is Solving Crashes for Wii and GameCube Games]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/dolphin-emulator-is-solving-crashes-for-wii-and-gamecube-games/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-dolphin-logo-over-a-screenshot-of-mario-galaxy-2.jpg" length="133" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It's gotten a lot better.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Dolphin is probably one of the biggest game emulation projects out there. It started years ago, and while the task of emulating most Wii and GameCube games is a hard one, developers have made great progress to the point that most computers and smartphones can play these old, but gold, titles. Now, the latest progress report has shown it's gotten a lot better recently.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 18:40:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/dolphin-emulator-is-solving-crashes-for-wii-and-gamecube-games/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why the iPhone Air Is the Most Important iPhone You’ll Never Buy]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-the-iphone-air-is-the-most-important-iphone-youll-never-buy/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-air-partial-x-ray-shot.jpg" length="2338" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone Air]]></category><category><![CDATA[battery]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            I'm not buying it, either.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I don’t want an iPhone Air, I’m buying the iPhone 17 Pro instead. The Air’s drawbacks just aren’t worth it to me; I don’t want an ultra-thin body at the cost of battery life and camera.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 18:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-the-iphone-air-is-the-most-important-iphone-youll-never-buy/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy One UI 8 Update Release Schedule Revealed]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/samsung-reveals-when-your-galaxy-will-get-android-16/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/a-stylized-layout-featuring-the-android-16-logo-one-ui-8-in-the-center-and-several-samsung-phones-side-by-side.png" length="2010" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Here's when your phone or tablet should get Android 16. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
